==English==
===Noun phrase===
'''girl friend''' (''plural'' '''girl friends''')

#A female friend, especially a woman's.

====Usage notes====
*The spelling of '''girl friend''' as two words is used to distinguish this term from '''[[girlfriend]]''', a girl or woman to whom one has a romantic attachment.<!--This is true in the UK, at least.  Does US usage spell it as one word anyway?-->